com.vmware.vapi.std

Class LocalizationParam

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vapi.std.LocalizationParam
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure, java.io.Serializable

    public final class LocalizationParam
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure
    This class holds a single message parameter and formatting settings for it. The class has fields for String, long, double, date time and nested messages. Only one will be used depending on the type of data sent. For date, double and long it is possible to set additional formatting details. This class was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        public NestedLocalizableMessage getL()
        Nested localizable value associated with the parameter. This is useful construct to convert to human readable localized form enumeration class and boolean values. It can also be used for proper handling of pluralization and gender forms in localization. Recursive NestedLocalizableMessage instances can be used for localizing short lists of items. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. this property will be set when nested localization message value is used.

        The current value of the property.
